	<head>
	<!--new file for 2012; did not exist in 2011.-->
		<title>URL to Event</title>
		<concept language="en-us" metaFormat="osm" metaVersion="1.1" text="URL to Event" audience="submission" path="/record/resources/relation/@url" deftn="A web address that links to the event associated with the item."/>
	</head>
	<bestPractices>
		<practice >This field is required.</practice>
		<practice>Begin all URLs with the correct Internet protocol like http:// or https:// etc.</practice>
		<practice link1="Example" style1="bold" link2="http://www.agu.org/cgi-bin/wais?ss=G53C-05" url2="http://www.agu.org/cgi-bin/wais?ss=G53C-05">Example: AGU page -  http://www.agu.org/cgi-bin/wais?ss=G53C-05.</practice>

	<!--2011 OS submission form version when the form was used for cataloging
		<practice>This field is optional and free-text.</practice>
		<practice>Use this field to provide access to a resource when no resource is uploaded to OpenSky.</practice>
		<practice>When a resource has been uploaded, use this field to provide additional information</practice>
		<practice>Begin all URLs with the correct Internet protocol like http:// or https:// etc.</practice>
		<practice>For online works, use the URL for the resource's landing page over the URL to the resource itself. This landing page typically precedes the actual work and provides additional bibliographic and other resource information.</practice>
		<practice>For online works that do not have a landing page, use the URL to the resource itself.</practice>
		<practice link1="Example" style1="bold" link2="http://journals.ametsoc.org/doi/abs/10.1175/2008JAS2830.1" url2="http://journals.ametsoc.org/doi/abs/10.1175/2008JAS2830.1">Example: landing page -  http://journals.ametsoc.org/doi/abs/10.1175/2008JAS2830.1.</practice>
		<practice link1="Example" style1="bold" link2="https://www.meted.ucar.edu/training_module.php?id=722" url2="https://www.meted.ucar.edu/training_module.php?id=722">Example: no landing page -  https://www.meted.ucar.edu/training_module.php?id=722.</practice>
-->
	</bestPractices>
</opml>
